let obj = {
  name: "obj",
  func1: function () {
    function fn1() {
      console.log(this, 1);
    }
    fn2 = () => {
      console.log(this, 2);
    };
    fn1();
    fn2();
  },
  fun2: () => {
    function fun1() {
      console.log(this, 3);
    }
    fun2 = () => {
      console.log(this, 4);
    };
    fun1();
    fun2();
  },
};
obj.func1();
obj.fun2();
